Kernel commands switches
-----------------------------
1 or single - enter single user mode

n - runlevel-n

init=/bin/bash - load /bin/bash instead of /sbin/init process

root=/dev/sdXX - lets the system boot to a different root partition.

ro - boot system in read-only mode. (can be used to run fsck)

debug - prints a more verbose output of the kernel loading status

selinux 0 or 1 - disables/enables selinux module
